parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of braking power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on intermittently
the ABS system fails to function
the brake pedal pulsates or goes to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
and the traction control system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear main seal can cause oil to leak onto the clutch and exhaust system, leading to potential fires and damage to the engine and transmission.
symptoms: Oil leaks onto the clutch and exhaust system
causing damage to the engine and transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor design of the driver's side wiper can cause a large portion of the windshield to remain unswept, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiper fails to sweep a large portion of the windshield
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the washer nozzle return valve can cause washer fluid to fail to reach the windshield, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Washer fluid fails to reach the windshield
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leakage at the Seam
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank leakage can cause fuel to spill onto the exhaust pipe, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor
fuel leaking from the seam of the fuel tank
fuel dripping onto the exhaust pipe
fuel puddles on the garage floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to lose awareness of their speed, potentially leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer becomes inoperable
the speedometer needle does not move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of the carburetor cable can cause fuel to spill, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leakage from the carburetor cable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle bursts into flames
white smoke emits from the tailpipe
the engine compartment is damaged
and the vehicle is unable to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear main seal failure can cause oil to leak onto the exhaust system, leading to a potential fire hazard.
symptoms: Oil leaks onto the exhaust system
the vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
and the rear main seal fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catalytic converter failure can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental concerns and potential health risks.
symptoms: The catalytic converter fails
the vehicle emits excessive pollutants
and the transmission shift lock release button locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle's wiring harness to melt, leading to a potential fire hazard.
symptoms: The alternator wiring harness melts
the electrical system fails
and the vehicle's safety design (fuseable link) does not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Emissions problems can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental concerns and potential health risks.
symptoms: The vehicle runs extremely rich
the engine consumes excessive amounts of oil
and the emissions system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system problems can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental concerns and potential health risks.
symptoms: The exhaust system fails
the vehicle emits excessive pollutants
and the exhaust smell/fumes enter the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
and the vehicle is unable to operate.
